This is a pencil implementation of SRAD (which is part of the Heart Wall application). The heart wall application tracks movement of a mouse heart.

The following are the command parameters to the application:
0) pgm file name.
1) Number of iterations. Needs to be integer > 0.
2) Saturation coefficient. Needs to be float > 0.
3) Number of rows in the output image. Needs to be integer > 0.
4) Number of columns in the output image. Needs to be integer > 0.

Example:
  ./c_srad data/image.pgm 100 0.5 502 458
